# claude-multipane config — copy to ~/.claude/panes.conf and edit.
# One project per line (whitespace-separated):
#
#   <name>  <main-worktree-path>  <main-branch>  <pane-count>  <tmux-target-prefix>
#
#   name                project label (also the git-worktree prefix)
#   main-worktree-path  the checked-out repo (the "main"/integration worktree)
#   main-branch         branch new pane worktrees fork from (e.g. main, develop)
#   pane-count          how many panes/worktrees to create
#   tmux-target-prefix  "<session>:<window>", e.g. xyz:1  -> panes xyz:1.1 .. .N
#
# Pane worktrees are derived as <main-worktree-path>_pane1 .. _paneN on
# branches pane1 .. paneN. `bin/setup-panes.sh <name>` creates them + the panes.
#
# Example — a project "xyz", 4 panes, forking from main:
xyz  /Users/you/dev/xyz  main  4  xyz:1
